-- 
Cnooc Bohai Oilfield Had Leak This Month, South Weekend Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-30T10:17:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/cnooc-bohai-oilfield-had-leak-this-month-south-weekend-reports.html
Cnooc Ltd. (883) ’s Penglai 19-3 oilfield
in Bohai Bay had a leak around June 10, the South Weekend
newspaper  reported , citing people it didn’t identify.  Authorities discovered a spill measuring 3 kilometers (1.9
miles) by 30 meters in the sea, according to the report.
Authorities have cleaned up the oil, it said.  ConocoPhillips (COP)  is
the operator of the field, according to South Weekend.  Calls made to Cnooc’s Beijing-based spokesman, Jiang Yongzhi, and ConocoPhillips’s Beijing office weren’t answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Winnie Zhu in Shanghai at 
 wzhu4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alexander Kwiatkowski at 
 akwiatkowsk2@bloomberg.net  